1
00:00:22,500 --> 00:00:26,333
<i>(Usagi)</i>
<i>Chibi‐Usa... Are you done yet?</i>

2
00:00:26,400 --> 00:00:30,066
<i>(Luna)</i>
<i>Nice job, Chibi‐Usa! It looks</i>
<i>exactly like her!</i>

3
00:00:30,100 --> 00:00:31,800
(Chibi‐Usa)
[giggle] You really think so?

4
00:00:31,833 --> 00:00:36,600
Hey! How much longer
is this gonna take?

5
00:00:36,633 --> 00:00:39,333
[groan] I'm getting tired...

6
00:00:39,400 --> 00:00:40,633
Stop moving and sit straight!

7
00:00:40,666 --> 00:00:42,633
This assignment is due tomorrow.

8
00:00:42,666 --> 00:00:45,500
But I've been stuck sitting
still like this for hours!

9
00:00:45,566 --> 00:00:49,766
I said I'd treat
you to pork buns.

10
00:00:49,800 --> 00:00:52,900
Sheesh... using my
weakness against me!

11
00:00:52,933 --> 00:00:54,966
Now, try to keep
still, will you?

12
00:00:55,000 --> 00:00:57,833
Fine, but how far along are you?

13
00:00:57,900 --> 00:00:59,266
Argh! What is that!?

14
00:00:59,300 --> 00:01:01,306
Hey! Go sit on the couch
like I told you!

15
00:01:01,306 --> 00:01:03,940
[grunts]
Stop!

16
00:01:03,973 --> 00:01:08,273
You're not trying to tell me
that this hideous looking
creature is supposed to be me,
are you?!

17
00:01:08,306 --> 00:01:11,006
Did you see anyone else posing?

18
00:01:11,073 --> 00:01:13,240
I think it's coming
along really well, Usagi.

19
00:01:13,273 --> 00:01:17,306
Argh! There's no
way I'm this ugly!

20
00:01:17,306 --> 00:01:19,406
You've never looked in the
mirror, have you?

21
00:01:19,440 --> 00:01:20,506
What was that!?

22
00:01:27,973 --> 00:01:38,006
♪

23
00:01:38,006 --> 00:01:58,006
♪

24
00:01:58,006 --> 00:02:18,013
♪

25
00:02:18,013 --> 00:02:38,113
♪

26
00:02:38,113 --> 00:02:52,146
♪

27
00:02:58,246 --> 00:03:04,486
<i>(Usagi)</i>
<i>Don't Lose Sight of Your Dreams:</i>
<i>The Mirror of Truth</i>

28
00:03:05,420 --> 00:03:11,120
These are great, but for the
record& I still think you
should go back and redo that
drawing of yours!

29
00:03:11,153 --> 00:03:14,353
Hey! Are you even listening?

30
00:03:14,420 --> 00:03:17,120
I promised you pork buns
and you got pork buns.

31
00:03:17,153 --> 00:03:20,186
So I get to decide what
to do with the picture.

32
00:03:20,253 --> 00:03:22,153
Hm?

33
00:03:23,153 --> 00:03:26,853
<i>(Chibi‐Usa)</i>
<i>Look! A street artist!</i>

34
00:03:32,320 --> 00:03:35,653
[amazed gasps]

35
00:03:35,653 --> 00:03:39,153
<i>(Chibi‐Usa)</i>
<i>It looks just like her!</i>

36
00:03:39,186 --> 00:03:41,786
That's how you paint
a person's face...

37
00:03:41,820 --> 00:03:43,486
...You should take
some notes.

38
00:03:43,486 --> 00:03:44,653
[grunt]

39
00:03:44,653 --> 00:03:47,486
Okay, it's done.

40
00:03:47,486 --> 00:03:51,153
Oh my. It doesn't
look anything like me.

41
00:03:51,186 --> 00:03:52,353
‐Huh?
‐Huh?

42
00:03:52,420 --> 00:03:55,320
Especially in the upper face.
I know I have bigger eyes.

43
00:03:55,353 --> 00:03:57,286
‐Yes, you do!
‐Yes, you do!

44
00:03:57,320 --> 00:03:59,153
And I'm sure my nose is sharper.

45
00:03:59,153 --> 00:04:02,993
You think so? Because I
tried to pay close attention
to those things.

46
00:04:03,026 --> 00:04:05,660
Hold on! Why are you
complaining?

47
00:04:05,660 --> 00:04:07,660
That painting looks
exactly like you!

48
00:04:07,660 --> 00:04:08,993
Uh...

49
00:04:08,993 --> 00:04:11,160
Shut up! No one asked
for your opinion!

50
00:04:11,193 --> 00:04:12,493
‐Yeah, shut up!
‐Yeah, shut up!

51
00:04:12,526 --> 00:04:14,026
You shush!

52
00:04:14,093 --> 00:04:16,293
<i>His painting's ugly. I'm much</i>
<i>more beautiful than that.</i>

53
00:04:16,326 --> 00:04:17,026
<i>(friends)</i>
<i>‐Yeah, she's right!</i>
<i>‐Yeah, she's right!</i>

54
00:04:17,093 --> 00:04:19,293
This argument sounds familiar.

55
00:04:19,326 --> 00:04:21,660
<i>(Kamoi Tanaka)</i>
<i>Excuse me...</i>

56
00:04:21,660 --> 00:04:22,693
[angry grunts]

57
00:04:22,760 --> 00:04:25,526
Honestly, I think the portrait's
a good likeness.

58
00:04:25,593 --> 00:04:28,760
But if it isn't what you wanted,
then so be it ‐‐ you don't have
to pay me.

59
00:04:28,793 --> 00:04:31,826
Then I'm not paying!
Let's go, ladies.

60
00:04:31,860 --> 00:04:32,593
‐Humph!
‐Humph!

61
00:04:33,459 --> 00:04:36,026
Wow, talk about pretty
nasty customers.

62
00:04:36,093 --> 00:04:37,993
[sigh]

63
00:04:37,993 --> 00:04:41,093
(Usagi / Chibi‐Usa)
Sorry! Did we just make that
situation a lot worse?

64
00:04:41,126 --> 00:04:42,993
Don't worry about it!

65
00:04:42,993 --> 00:04:45,526
Would you like a portrait
of one of you?

66
00:04:45,593 --> 00:04:48,460
Oh no...

67
00:04:48,493 --> 00:04:50,026
Oh, I won't charge you anything.

68
00:04:50,093 --> 00:04:52,926
It's my way of saying thanks
for trying to help me.

69
00:04:55,993 --> 00:04:58,693
<i>(Ves‐Ves)</i>
<i>Listen... you've given us</i>
<i>nothing but bad leads.</i>

70
00:04:58,760 --> 00:05:02,700
Palla‐Palla thinks you need to
do a much better job.

71
00:05:02,766 --> 00:05:05,166
Yeah, stop messing
around, or we'll eat you!

72
00:05:05,166 --> 00:05:06,500
We mean it this time...

73
00:05:06,500 --> 00:05:08,333
<i>(Zirconia)</i>
<i>You're the one's that</i>
<i>need to do a better job!</i>

74
00:05:08,333 --> 00:05:09,200
Hm?

75
00:05:10,333 --> 00:05:13,666
Whining and playing ‐
that's all you girls ever do.

76
00:05:13,700 --> 00:05:16,033
<i>You lazy, good‐for‐nothings!</i>

77
00:05:16,100 --> 00:05:18,200
<i>What happened to finding</i>
<i>the Golden Mirror?</i>

78
00:05:18,266 --> 00:05:21,333
Here's the next target.
Now get to work!

79
00:05:21,333 --> 00:05:23,433
Hm?

80
00:05:23,466 --> 00:05:25,166
<i>(Ves‐Ves)</i>
<i>He looks like a painter.</i>

81
00:05:25,166 --> 00:05:26,133
<i>(Cere‐Cere)</i>
<i>A painter??</i>

82
00:05:26,166 --> 00:05:28,600
Step aside, I'll be
taking this one.

83
00:05:28,633 --> 00:05:29,666
[confused gasps]

84
00:05:29,700 --> 00:05:32,000
A painter...

85
00:05:33,300 --> 00:05:37,633
(Ves‐Ves)
You're the laziest person I
know. Why do you want to work
all of a sudden?

86
00:05:37,666 --> 00:05:40,533
<i>(Palla‐Palla)</i>
<i>What happened to her?</i>

87
00:05:40,600 --> 00:05:43,133
Tell us, what are you up to?

88
00:05:43,166 --> 00:05:45,466
I'm not up to anything!

89
00:05:45,500 --> 00:05:50,666
I just thought it'd be nice to
have a young man paint a
beautiful portrait of me in all
my lovely glory.

90
00:05:50,666 --> 00:05:53,333
Uh...

91
00:05:53,333 --> 00:05:56,633
[flirty giggling]

92
00:06:02,540 --> 00:06:05,773
You're so good...

93
00:06:05,806 --> 00:06:09,673
But really, did you have
to pose with a pork bun?!

94
00:06:09,673 --> 00:06:15,006
I just thought my face would
look happier if I were eating
something tasty and delicious.
Y'know?

95
00:06:15,006 --> 00:06:16,106
[grunt]

96
00:06:16,140 --> 00:06:17,940
Hey, whatever makes
her comfortable

97
00:06:17,973 --> 00:06:18,840
But she looks‐‐!

98
00:06:18,840 --> 00:06:21,006
It's not your portrait,
so be quiet!

99
00:06:21,040 --> 00:06:22,606
Back off, Usagi!

100
00:06:22,640 --> 00:06:25,040
They really do seem to
make you happy, though.

101
00:06:25,106 --> 00:06:27,873
That's 'cuz& they're great.

102
00:06:27,940 --> 00:06:30,440
[gulp] Yeah, I bet they are.

103
00:06:31,606 --> 00:06:34,940
[stomach growling]

104
00:06:37,040 --> 00:06:38,606
‐Mr. Kamoi!
‐Mr. Kamoi!

105
00:06:38,640 --> 00:06:44,540
I‐I'm fine... It's just that& I
haven't eaten anything& in the
past few& days.

106
00:06:44,606 --> 00:06:47,373
What!? Give him a
pork bun! Stat!

107
00:06:47,440 --> 00:06:49,506
Uhhh... About that...

108
00:06:49,506 --> 00:06:50,673
Seriously?

109
00:06:50,706 --> 00:06:53,506
<i>(Usagi)</i>
<i>[screams]</i>

110
00:06:53,540 --> 00:06:55,540
<i>(Chibi‐Usa)</i>
<i>Usagi! The food's on fire!</i>

111
00:06:55,606 --> 00:06:57,040
What do I do!?

112
00:06:57,106 --> 00:07:00,980
Where's Mom?! She's never home
when I really need her!

113
00:07:01,680 --> 00:07:04,446
Here it is. “Bon appetit. ”

114
00:07:04,480 --> 00:07:08,680
I'll understand if you'd
rather not eat it.

115
00:07:08,680 --> 00:07:11,013
No, I'll eat it!

116
00:07:11,013 --> 00:07:13,013
That's some appetite!

117
00:07:13,046 --> 00:07:15,346
<i>(Usagi)</i>
<i>You really were</i>
<i>hungry, weren't you?</i>

118
00:07:15,346 --> 00:07:17,146
Oh, sorry.

119
00:07:17,180 --> 00:07:21,713
There's no need to apologize.
If you wanna eat her disgusting
fried rice, then go for it.

120
00:07:21,780 --> 00:07:23,346
Eh, watch it!

121
00:07:23,346 --> 00:07:26,446
I don't mean to be rude. But
why haven't you been eating?

122
00:07:26,480 --> 00:07:30,113
I'm embarrassed to say
this, but I'm broke.

123
00:07:30,146 --> 00:07:31,346
‐Huh?
‐Huh?

124
00:07:31,346 --> 00:07:33,513
So I really
appreciate the meal!

125
00:07:33,513 --> 00:07:35,313
(Usagi / Chibi‐Usa)
You're welcome. Glad
you liked it.

126
00:07:35,346 --> 00:07:38,346
So does this mean
artists don't make money?

127
00:07:38,380 --> 00:07:41,846
Others might, but I get into
arguments with my customers.

128
00:07:41,846 --> 00:07:45,546
They're often not happy with
their portraits, so I usually
don't get paid.

129
00:07:45,613 --> 00:07:48,346
Couldn't you just paint them to
look a little prettier then?

130
00:07:48,346 --> 00:07:53,213
Yeah, I know I could
make money that way but&

131
00:07:53,280 --> 00:07:57,213
If I did that, could I still
call myself an artist?

132
00:07:57,280 --> 00:08:02,620
I know& getting paid is
important, but I can't sacrifice
my integrity.

133
00:08:02,653 --> 00:08:04,353
I guess you're right.

134
00:08:04,386 --> 00:08:06,686
I have to stay true to my dream.

135
00:08:06,686 --> 00:08:10,386
I want my work as an artist, to
be my legacy, not my name.

136
00:08:10,453 --> 00:08:13,686
<i>(Thinking)</i>
<i>[sigh] He's an artist,</i>
<i>alright.</i>

137
00:08:13,720 --> 00:08:18,453
Mr. Kamoi, if you have a sec,
there's something I'd like you
to take a look at.

138
00:08:20,153 --> 00:08:22,020
Is this any good?

139
00:08:22,053 --> 00:08:24,853
Why're you showing him
that! It's embarrassing!

140
00:08:24,886 --> 00:08:26,353
Whaddaya think? And be honest!

141
00:08:26,353 --> 00:08:30,386
<i>Hmm... It could usea</i>
<i>little more wor.</i>

142
00:08:30,453 --> 00:08:31,886
I told you...

143
00:08:31,953 --> 00:08:35,020
But... I also think your
picture's great!

144
00:08:35,020 --> 00:08:38,120
From looking at it, I
can tell how much you
love your big sister.

145
00:08:38,153 --> 00:08:41,186
[gasps]

146
00:08:51,553 --> 00:08:55,486
What's wrong? You've been
staring at the mirror for
a while now.

147
00:08:55,520 --> 00:08:59,686
Did you know that mirrors can
only show you the truth?

148
00:08:59,720 --> 00:09:02,993
What do your eyes see when you
look at your reflection?

149
00:09:03,026 --> 00:09:06,526
[sigh] I'm not really sure.

150
00:09:06,526 --> 00:09:08,360
Oh?

151
00:09:08,360 --> 00:09:12,560
I guess I'm learning that there
are lots of people who can't see
themselves as they really are.

152
00:09:12,626 --> 00:09:15,293
You could be right about that.

153
00:09:15,326 --> 00:09:19,026
Or is the face in the
mirror not true at all?

154
00:09:19,026 --> 00:09:22,960
Could it be that the person I
see is not the real me?

155
00:09:22,993 --> 00:09:24,893
No, that's the real you.

156
00:09:24,960 --> 00:09:27,460
Like I said, Mirrors
reflect the truth.

157
00:09:27,493 --> 00:09:32,560
It's people's hearts that
distort the images ‐ to match
the beauty or ugliness they see
in themselves

158
00:09:32,626 --> 00:09:34,193
Hm...

159
00:09:35,493 --> 00:09:38,793
(Rei)
Wow! He's really good.

160
00:09:38,826 --> 00:09:41,526
This captures the
real you, Usagi.

161
00:09:41,560 --> 00:09:43,860
I don't know...

162
00:09:43,893 --> 00:09:46,860
Look. Don't you think my big
eyes are cuter than that?

163
00:09:46,893 --> 00:09:49,493
Is he always at the park?

164
00:09:49,526 --> 00:09:50,860
I think so.

165
00:09:50,893 --> 00:09:52,860
This is cool. I want
him to paint me.

166
00:09:52,893 --> 00:09:57,293
I have a lot of photos of
myself. But having a portrait
painted would be special.

167
00:09:57,326 --> 00:09:58,860
Mhm!

168
00:09:58,926 --> 00:10:01,233
...And look at my nose. Don't
you think it's a bit cuter
than in the picture?

169
00:10:01,266 --> 00:10:04,466
Hey, guys, let's get
him to paint each of us!

170
00:10:04,466 --> 00:10:06,300
(All)
Yeah!

171
00:10:06,300 --> 00:10:10,666
Oh, and look at my coloring.
I think my skin tone is a
little more fair.

172
00:10:11,466 --> 00:10:19,133
<i>♪ Sailor Moon</i>

173
00:10:28,333 --> 00:10:32,000
<i>♪ Sailor Moon</i>

174
00:10:47,133 --> 00:10:49,266
How do you do?

175
00:10:49,300 --> 00:10:53,433
You must be Kamoi Tanaka. I've
heard so much about you...

176
00:10:53,466 --> 00:10:56,833
...and I was eager to come meet
you face to face.

177
00:10:56,900 --> 00:11:00,640
You have a reputation as a
skilled artist&

178
00:11:00,640 --> 00:11:04,106
& so I've come today with a
very tempting proposition.

179
00:11:04,140 --> 00:11:06,340
Listen close&

180
00:11:06,406 --> 00:11:11,740
I have decided that I will pose
for you and you shall have the
honor of painting my portrait.

181
00:11:11,773 --> 00:11:17,406
[haughty laugh] Now please stay
calm. There's no need to get
so excited!

182
00:11:17,440 --> 00:11:20,140
Excuse me! I haven't
finished my proposal!

183
00:11:20,140 --> 00:11:24,140
This isn't the right setting,
so I want you to paint me in
my mansion .

184
00:11:24,140 --> 00:11:25,940
[groan]

185
00:11:25,973 --> 00:11:29,806
I'll buy you any art supplies
you desire. Money is no object!

186
00:11:29,806 --> 00:11:31,140
I hear you&

187
00:11:31,140 --> 00:11:33,473
And...?

188
00:11:33,473 --> 00:11:38,140
I get the sense you've inherited
great wealth. But it's rude to
flaunt what you have, when you
didn't earn it yourself.

189
00:11:38,140 --> 00:11:39,406
[gulp]

190
00:11:39,440 --> 00:11:43,306
I'm sorry. You'll have to hire
someone else to paint you.

191
00:11:43,340 --> 00:11:45,940
[grunt]

192
00:11:45,973 --> 00:11:48,640
<i>(Thinking)</i>
<i>He is tougher than I expected...</i>

193
00:11:48,640 --> 00:11:50,906
<i>...In that case...</i>

194
00:11:50,940 --> 00:11:53,940
Forgive me. I got carried away.

195
00:11:53,973 --> 00:11:57,240
The truth is, last year
I lost my father.

196
00:11:57,273 --> 00:11:59,240
He was a devoted
art dealer.

197
00:11:59,273 --> 00:12:04,446
It was my father's desire to
help struggling, talented
artists like yourself.

198
00:12:04,480 --> 00:12:08,980
He believed in dreams.
I want to carry on his
mission...

199
00:12:08,980 --> 00:12:11,280
His passionate
vision is now mine.

200
00:12:11,313 --> 00:12:16,080
It would fulfill my dream if
you'd come to my home and paint
to your heart's content.

201
00:12:16,113 --> 00:12:18,513
[sob]

202
00:12:20,946 --> 00:12:24,180
<i>(thinking)</i>
<i>I've got him, now.</i>

203
00:12:24,313 --> 00:12:25,980
Where does your
artist friend work?

204
00:12:25,980 --> 00:12:27,480
We're almost there.

205
00:12:28,446 --> 00:12:30,246
[excited chatter]

206
00:12:30,280 --> 00:12:32,246
[gasp] He's gone!

207
00:12:32,313 --> 00:12:34,413
That's strange,
where did he go?

208
00:12:34,446 --> 00:12:37,646
Maybe he decided to call
it a day, and go home.

209
00:12:37,680 --> 00:12:38,813
Too bad...

210
00:12:38,813 --> 00:12:40,613
<i>(Rei)</i>
<i>You've got to be kidding!</i>

211
00:12:40,646 --> 00:12:44,980
I came all the way here to get
my portrait done! Now you're
saying he just disappeared?

212
00:12:44,980 --> 00:12:47,580
Come on, Usagi!
What's going on here?!

213
00:12:47,613 --> 00:12:49,613
I'm telling you he
was here yesterday!

214
00:12:49,646 --> 00:12:53,413
Oh really? Isn't it convenient
that only you got a portrait
done!

215
00:12:53,446 --> 00:12:55,313
You don't have to get
so worked up about it.

216
00:12:55,313 --> 00:12:56,680
Yeah, that's right.

217
00:12:56,746 --> 00:12:58,746
Are you guys kidding!?

218
00:12:58,780 --> 00:13:03,786
<i>If artists miss this moment...</i>
<i>to paint this sweet yet</i>
<i>beautiful Rei...</i>

219
00:13:03,820 --> 00:13:09,620
<i>what else in the world could</i>
<i>they possibly paint that would</i>
<i>be as fulfilling?</i>

220
00:13:09,653 --> 00:13:12,086
Uh, Rei...?

221
00:13:12,120 --> 00:13:14,253
Now come on! Let's split
up and look for him!

222
00:13:14,286 --> 00:13:16,853
Uh, yeah, sure.

223
00:13:18,586 --> 00:13:22,453
This is ridiculous. We don't
have any idea where to start
looking.

224
00:13:22,486 --> 00:13:25,953
How are we ever gonna find him?

225
00:13:25,986 --> 00:13:28,120
Our only clue is this
painting...

226
00:13:28,153 --> 00:13:31,820
but it's not like he wrote his
address on it, or anything else
helpful.

227
00:13:31,820 --> 00:13:35,753
[sigh] Hey! Stop slacking!

228
00:13:35,786 --> 00:13:36,820
Huh?

229
00:13:37,153 --> 00:13:40,086
Hold on, what is this?

230
00:13:40,120 --> 00:13:41,920
It's a letter...

231
00:13:41,953 --> 00:13:43,020
What?

232
00:13:43,086 --> 00:13:46,653
“Dear Miss Usagi, Thank you
for your hospitality...

233
00:13:46,686 --> 00:13:51,320
I've passed out from hunger
before, but that was the first
time someone took me to their
home.

234
00:13:51,320 --> 00:13:55,086
<i>& You made me feel welcome, and</i>
<i>cooked a hearty meal for me.</i>
<i>For that I'm eternally grateful.</i>

235
00:13:55,120 --> 00:14:00,353
<i>I was too embarrassed, and too</i>
<i>hungry, to say all of this to</i>
<i>you.</i>

236
00:14:00,420 --> 00:14:06,693
<i>But I'll never forget the taste</i>
<i>of that fried rice for as long</i>
<i>as I live. Thank you."</i>

237
00:14:06,760 --> 00:14:10,293
